# 9. Why This Works

Between any two common elements:

* You cannot switch except at the common value.
* Therefore there are exactly two candidate path sums.
* Choosing the larger one cannot reduce any future answer because future decisions begin after the common element.

Thus, making the locally optimal choice at every common element leads to the globally optimal result.

